    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "An ocular flush really means flushing your eyes with a mild saline solution to wash out any debris and bacteria causing that discharge. Forget the simple lubricating drops; look specifically for drops containing a mild antiseptic like Bacitracin, but only use them as directed. If the redness persists after a 24-hour flush and a couple of drops, you're probably dealing with something that requires a more potent, fast-acting treatment.",
