      "content": "Bacitracin is fine for a few days to knock down the infection, but don't overuse it; stick to twice daily to give your eyes a chance to heal. Never use standard contact lens solution for a flush, as it's not sterile enough, so buy a dedicated, preservative-free saline eyewash. Trust me, a little bit of targeted treatment will get you back to your screen faster than worrying about it!",
      "source": "target",
